1
00:00:56,634 --> 00:01:00,229
BASED ON REAL EVENTS

2
00:02:12,677 --> 00:02:15,043
Mateo, son,
what are you doing there?

3
00:02:21,419 --> 00:02:23,546
You're absolutely frozen, darling.

4
00:02:25,022 --> 00:02:27,183
Did you have another nightmare?

5
00:02:28,392 --> 00:02:30,690
Come on, get back into bed.

6
00:02:33,731 --> 00:02:35,164
That's it.

7
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:37,559
Can I sleep with you?

8
00:02:37,802 --> 00:02:41,465
Don't you worry, okay?
I'm going to get a glass of water.

9
00:02:51,716 --> 00:02:55,880
THE MUD BOY

10
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:31,779
Come on, wake up.

11
00:03:35,593 --> 00:03:37,584
I've got to go.

12
00:03:37,895 --> 00:03:40,056
This bed is so comfortable.

13
00:04:19,403 --> 00:04:21,633
Come on, get up,
there's warm bread.

14
00:04:28,279 --> 00:04:30,213
Come on, move it!

15
00:04:30,348 --> 00:04:32,339
Three get off here.

16
00:04:42,293 --> 00:04:43,988
Let's see.

17
00:04:52,603 --> 00:04:55,572
What do you dream about
that scares you so much?

18
00:04:57,875 --> 00:05:00,708
You dream about what happened
that night, don't you?

19
00:05:03,447 --> 00:05:06,075
Roque said he was going
to teach me a job.

20
00:05:06,384 --> 00:05:10,115
Did he? What's wrong? Don't you want
to be my assistant anymore?

21
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:25,031
Aren't you going to say goodbye?

22
00:05:26,103 --> 00:05:27,832
It doesn't matter.

23
00:05:32,810 --> 00:05:35,040
I'm still worried about Mateo.

24
00:05:35,312 --> 00:05:38,247
You should find work for the kid.

25
00:05:39,417 --> 00:05:41,248
It's about time
he brought some money in.

26
00:05:41,385 --> 00:05:42,784
Doing what?

27
00:05:42,887 --> 00:05:46,288
Rolling cigarettes 17 hours a day
for one peso a week?

28
00:05:47,725 --> 00:05:49,625
I want something different.

29
00:05:49,894 --> 00:05:52,692
What do you want,
to turn the boy into a gentleman?

30
00:05:55,399 --> 00:05:58,800
At least you'd get him off the streets,
where he's in danger.

31
00:06:01,539 --> 00:06:04,064
You're spoiling him, Estela.

32
00:06:04,408 --> 00:06:07,707
You know what I think,
the boy needs a bit of discipline.

33
00:06:12,650 --> 00:06:14,117
You sleep with me when it suits you...

34
00:06:14,218 --> 00:06:16,948
and you think you have the right
to tell me how to bring up my son?

35
00:06:17,054 --> 00:06:21,218
Hey, don't speak like that,
as if I only came by once a month.

36
00:06:21,358 --> 00:06:23,189
Come on...

37
00:06:25,963 --> 00:06:27,692
After all...

38
00:06:29,366 --> 00:06:33,700
for several years now
it's suited me virtually every day.

39
00:07:25,122 --> 00:07:26,817
You won the race.

40
00:07:27,525 --> 00:07:30,187
-But look.
-Did you steal them?

41
00:07:31,095 --> 00:07:34,496
They're yours for two cents.
They'd be perfect for your mother.

42
00:07:36,901 --> 00:07:38,732
I don't have any money.

43
00:07:38,936 --> 00:07:40,733
They cost ten cents in the shop.

44
00:07:40,938 --> 00:07:43,372
If you like,
I'll show you how to get them.

45
00:07:44,141 --> 00:07:46,268
My mother says stealing is wrong.

46
00:07:46,377 --> 00:07:49,175
All mothers say that, idiot.
You're a coward.

47
00:07:49,914 --> 00:07:51,745
I'm not a coward.

48
00:08:07,164 --> 00:08:08,495
-Excuse me.
-Palacios...

49
00:08:08,632 --> 00:08:11,567
Bring me a strong coffee,
then tell me about it.

50
00:08:13,437 --> 00:08:15,632
And don't look at me like that!
You are not my mother.

51
00:08:15,739 --> 00:08:19,197
It's just you look
like the living dead, boss.

52
00:08:19,944 --> 00:08:22,310
That is exactly what I am.

53
00:08:33,157 --> 00:08:35,318
Are you looking for something, sir?

54
00:08:35,860 --> 00:08:38,954
-Shall I help with those cases?
-No, thanks.

55
00:08:42,733 --> 00:08:44,928
Do you want to earn twenty cents?

56
00:08:45,069 --> 00:08:47,162
Yes, of course.
Who doesn't?

57
00:08:47,338 --> 00:08:49,568
Come here. Look...

58
00:08:50,474 --> 00:08:52,237
I'm a photographer.

59
00:08:52,309 --> 00:08:55,801
I'd like to take some photos
of you with that girl.

60
00:08:55,913 --> 00:08:57,574
Do you know her?

61
00:09:13,931 --> 00:09:16,593
You're the most beautiful woman
in the neighborhood.

62
00:09:36,887 --> 00:09:39,048
Let's see.
Come over here.

63
00:09:41,892 --> 00:09:44,452
That's it, there.

64
00:09:44,962 --> 00:09:49,331
Together, look that way.

65
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:52,064
Very good.
What a pretty face!

66
00:09:52,169 --> 00:09:55,297
That's right. Wait here.
I'm going to prepare the equipment.

67
00:09:58,142 --> 00:10:00,440
Give me the money without her seeing.

68
00:10:10,354 --> 00:10:12,822
Let's see, get a bit closer to her.

69
00:10:12,923 --> 00:10:15,153
A bit more. Really close.

70
00:10:15,225 --> 00:10:17,750
Right next to each other.

71
00:10:18,462 --> 00:10:21,954
Very good. But don't look at me,
look at each other.

72
00:10:22,733 --> 00:10:24,200
Let's see.

73
00:10:24,501 --> 00:10:26,526
Good, very good.

74
00:10:26,603 --> 00:10:30,130
Perfect. Let's see.
Now, give her a kiss.

75
00:10:30,708 --> 00:10:32,505
Give her a kiss.

76
00:10:34,378 --> 00:10:37,711
That's it.
Hold it there.

77
00:10:38,215 --> 00:10:42,083
Perfect. Very good, very good.

78
00:10:42,386 --> 00:10:46,186
Let's see, now pull her skirt down.

79
00:10:49,727 --> 00:10:51,820
Don't be afraid, pull it down.

80
00:10:56,633 --> 00:10:58,533
Go on, pull it down.

81
00:11:01,271 --> 00:11:03,967
That's it... More...

82
00:11:06,276 --> 00:11:07,675
Very good.

83
00:11:07,778 --> 00:11:11,077
Very good. Let's see, one more.

84
00:11:11,382 --> 00:11:14,749
Now, pull her knickers down.

85
00:11:17,321 --> 00:11:19,255
Go on, pull them down.

86
00:11:19,656 --> 00:11:21,886
Don't be afraid, pull them down.

87
00:11:25,429 --> 00:11:27,090
No, I don't want to!

88
00:11:30,434 --> 00:11:32,231
All right, stay there.

89
00:11:34,371 --> 00:11:36,965
Little devil!
Watch where you're running!

90
00:11:37,074 --> 00:11:38,473
Mateo!

91
00:11:38,909 --> 00:11:42,174
Come on, slacker!
Get to work, this is the last one.

92
00:11:42,946 --> 00:11:44,811
Go on, man, go on!

93
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:52,083
Be careful, son!

94
00:11:54,224 --> 00:11:57,352
I have enough work sewing clothes.
Don't make me wash them.

95
00:11:58,062 --> 00:11:59,859
Come on, help me pick them up.

96
00:11:59,963 --> 00:12:01,294
No.

97
00:12:01,398 --> 00:12:04,231
Mateo, help me, now! Come on.

98
00:12:05,736 --> 00:12:07,135
I don't want to.

99
00:12:07,237 --> 00:12:10,764
And what do you want,
for me to beat you, like Octavio says?

100
00:12:15,612 --> 00:12:18,479
What's up with you?
I work my fingers to the bone...

101
00:12:18,682 --> 00:12:20,843
to give you everything you need
and this is how you repay me?

102
00:12:30,527 --> 00:12:32,461
Where did you get this from?

103
00:12:33,697 --> 00:12:35,892
I can bring you money too...

104
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:38,797
Like Octavio does.

105
00:12:41,572 --> 00:12:44,507
Go to your room, right now.
Now, Mateo!

106
00:13:46,069 --> 00:13:48,970
Come on, Mateo, stop crying.
I won't punish you if you promise...

107
00:13:49,039 --> 00:13:52,202
-you'll never do it again.
-I'm scared, mum.

108
00:13:55,345 --> 00:13:57,210
Another nightmare?

109
00:13:58,582 --> 00:14:00,641
Listen, tomorrow
we're going to the hospital...

110
00:14:00,784 --> 00:14:03,412
-so the doctors can see you.
-No, no, mum.

111
00:14:03,620 --> 00:14:06,555
I don't want to tell anyone else,
just you. Promise me.

112
00:14:07,558 --> 00:14:10,550
Look, there's no need to feel ashamed.

113
00:14:11,061 --> 00:14:13,359
Lots of children have nightmares.

114
00:14:16,366 --> 00:14:19,028
But this time I wasn't asleep.

115
00:14:31,081 --> 00:14:32,912
What's this?

116
00:14:35,118 --> 00:14:36,949
Mateo, what's this?

117
00:14:37,521 --> 00:14:39,182
I found it.

118
00:14:40,524 --> 00:14:42,253
Look at me.

119
00:14:42,960 --> 00:14:45,428
The money you gave me,
did you find that too?

120
00:15:19,496 --> 00:15:21,760
I don't think he was raped,

121
00:15:21,965 --> 00:15:24,866
but I won't know for sure
until the autopsy is done.

122
00:15:35,512 --> 00:15:37,776
You can't go on like this, Petrie.

123
00:15:38,315 --> 00:15:40,283
You need more sleep.

124
00:15:41,418 --> 00:15:45,286
You won't bring your wife back to life
by destroying yourself.

125
00:15:47,024 --> 00:15:49,458
It's not just that, Soria...

126
00:15:51,161 --> 00:15:54,688
The problem is the emptiness
that seems to invade all of us.

127
00:15:56,433 --> 00:15:58,492
It doesn't matter what we do.

128
00:15:59,503 --> 00:16:02,370
Every day a ship arrives
full of starving people.

129
00:16:06,510 --> 00:16:08,444
They live like animals...

130
00:16:09,713 --> 00:16:11,908
and so they become animals.

131
00:16:13,583 --> 00:16:15,551
You're wrong there.

132
00:16:16,486 --> 00:16:20,320
Animals aren't capable
of perversions like this.

133
00:16:39,109 --> 00:16:40,633
What do you think?

134
00:16:45,816 --> 00:16:47,477
Looks like magnesium.

135
00:16:54,358 --> 00:16:55,985
-Good morning.
-Yes?

136
00:17:01,131 --> 00:17:02,689
For you.

137
00:17:05,669 --> 00:17:07,159
What do you want?

138
00:17:07,871 --> 00:17:09,338
To come in.

139
00:17:10,674 --> 00:17:12,642
It's complicated.

140
00:17:12,709 --> 00:17:14,768
It's going to take a lot more than that.

141
00:17:15,045 --> 00:17:19,175
-Don't you understand my problem?
-That has nothing to do with us.

142
00:17:19,516 --> 00:17:22,679
-Is she the owner of the house?
-Mrs. Eulalia Galán, the owner.

143
00:17:22,819 --> 00:17:25,686
Superintendent Lautaro Petrie,
in charge of this case.

144
00:17:25,789 --> 00:17:27,256
Very well, lady.

145
00:17:27,457 --> 00:17:30,654
You say you gave the keys
to Mr. Luchessi and Mr. Marino,

146
00:17:30,861 --> 00:17:34,524
they returned them to you and told you
they'd found a dead body in the house,

147
00:17:34,798 --> 00:17:36,663
and you let them go.

148
00:17:36,767 --> 00:17:39,702
A real fright they got,
those two gentlemen.

149
00:17:40,303 --> 00:17:44,034
-Do you give the keys to just anyone?
-I've got to look after the shop.

150
00:17:44,207 --> 00:17:47,734
I give people the keys
and later they give them back to me.

151
00:17:47,944 --> 00:17:49,605
But just in case they forget,

152
00:17:49,713 --> 00:17:51,874
I write down all the addresses.

153
00:17:52,682 --> 00:17:55,981
You have all the details of the people
who have visited the house recently?

154
00:17:56,086 --> 00:17:58,020
Yes, of course, I have them here.

155
00:18:04,494 --> 00:18:06,724
Mr. Luchessi and Mr. Marino...

156
00:18:06,830 --> 00:18:09,321
Live in Colombres Street 642.

157
00:18:09,733 --> 00:18:12,429
They wanted to rent the house
as a painting studio.

158
00:18:12,636 --> 00:18:16,367
There are lots of artists
in the neighborhood: actors,

159
00:18:16,540 --> 00:18:19,475
-models...
-Any photographers?

160
00:18:23,613 --> 00:18:24,841
Yes.

161
00:18:25,649 --> 00:18:27,708
Yes. Mr. Garcés.

162
00:18:27,951 --> 00:18:30,442
He lives at Chile Street, 84.

163
00:18:30,554 --> 00:18:34,217
He visited the house two weeks ago,
he seemed very interested.

164
00:18:34,724 --> 00:18:37,215
Can we keep the notebook
to check the other details?

165
00:18:37,294 --> 00:18:40,491
Octavio!
How did this idiot get in here?

166
00:18:40,697 --> 00:18:43,860
Sorry, sir.
He must have slipped past.

167
00:18:49,673 --> 00:18:51,265
Is this yours?

168
00:18:52,909 --> 00:18:55,241
-No, it's not mine.
-All right.

169
00:18:55,479 --> 00:18:58,039
You and I have to talk
back at the police station.

170
00:19:00,517 --> 00:19:01,984
What is it, Palacios?

171
00:19:02,185 --> 00:19:04,983
Can't you even stop
scum like that getting in?

172
00:19:12,562 --> 00:19:14,689
Can I tell you something, mum?

173
00:19:16,433 --> 00:19:18,526
Of course you can.
Come here.

174
00:19:21,371 --> 00:19:22,531
What?

175
00:19:23,640 --> 00:19:26,108
I think they've killed
my friend Arturo.

176
00:19:26,843 --> 00:19:28,435
I saw it.

177
00:19:31,548 --> 00:19:33,243
Why do you say that?

178
00:19:33,583 --> 00:19:35,608
What did you see? Tell me.

179
00:19:38,321 --> 00:19:41,154
They beat him
and there was a lot of blood,

180
00:19:41,791 --> 00:19:44,919
then they hanged him by the neck
on the merry-go-round.

181
00:19:48,965 --> 00:19:50,523
Mateo...

182
00:19:51,735 --> 00:19:53,327
I think
you're still having nightmares...

183
00:19:53,403 --> 00:19:56,497
about what happened that night
when you were little.

184
00:19:59,376 --> 00:20:02,539
But that doesn't give you the right
to those tempers of yours,

185
00:20:03,580 --> 00:20:05,377
or to treat me bad.

186
00:20:11,588 --> 00:20:14,079
Are you going to tell me
where you got that?

187
00:20:19,529 --> 00:20:22,089
A man dropped it and I picked it up.

188
00:20:44,254 --> 00:20:47,485
Superintendent,
come and see this.

189
00:21:15,285 --> 00:21:17,879
What kind of man could do
something like this?

190
00:21:31,968 --> 00:21:33,492
Is everything okay?

191
00:21:34,204 --> 00:21:36,001
It's Mateo.

192
00:21:36,840 --> 00:21:39,274
He says he saw how they killed
a friend of his.

193
00:21:39,809 --> 00:21:41,276
-Today?
-Yes.

194
00:21:41,778 --> 00:21:43,712
I promised I wouldn't tell you, but...

195
00:21:43,880 --> 00:21:45,973
I don't know what's wrong with him.

196
00:21:49,552 --> 00:21:51,110
Let's go in.

197
00:22:06,002 --> 00:22:09,563
-And where did this come from?
-He said he found it.

198
00:22:14,144 --> 00:22:17,602
Today I saw a box like this one
in the house where they killed a boy.

199
00:22:18,715 --> 00:22:20,580
Your son is in serious trouble.

200
00:22:20,684 --> 00:22:23,050
Perhaps it was there he saw the murder.

201
00:22:23,186 --> 00:22:26,678
No, he says he saw it in a dream,
while he was here with me.

202
00:22:26,890 --> 00:22:30,155
And if your kid tells you he flew
right over to the other side of town,

203
00:22:30,226 --> 00:22:32,956
-do you believe him as well?
-Listen, Octavio.

204
00:22:33,630 --> 00:22:35,962
I know my son,
I know when he's lying.

205
00:22:36,166 --> 00:22:38,862
I'm sure there are bad things
going on in his head.

206
00:22:39,169 --> 00:22:40,534
Okay.

207
00:22:41,971 --> 00:22:46,237
Soria, the police doctor,
is an acquaintance of mine.

208
00:22:47,210 --> 00:22:50,976
Tomorrow we'll go to see him,
ask him to have a look at the boy.

209
00:22:54,250 --> 00:22:56,775
But we'll have to keep
an eye on him all the same.

210
00:22:57,187 --> 00:22:59,485
You've been too lenient with him.

211
00:23:07,497 --> 00:23:10,466
Darling, Octavio knows a doctor...

212
00:23:10,667 --> 00:23:12,567
who's going to have a look
at you tomorrow.

213
00:23:12,902 --> 00:23:14,767
You're a liar, mum!

214
00:23:15,004 --> 00:23:18,132
-You promised you wouldn't tell anyone!
-Don't speak to me like that, Mateo.

215
00:23:18,374 --> 00:23:21,810
And you! You can just keep out of it!

216
00:23:22,112 --> 00:23:24,603
-Mateo, please!
-Don't touch me!

217
00:23:25,415 --> 00:23:27,542
Calm down.
You see what he's like?

218
00:23:27,617 --> 00:23:29,608
-All right, let go of him.
-I'm going out...

219
00:23:29,719 --> 00:23:32,813
see if he calms down a bit.
Calm down!

220
00:23:33,156 --> 00:23:36,785
Listen to me, calm down!
You get a hold of him!

221
00:24:03,186 --> 00:24:04,744
Son!

222
00:24:06,890 --> 00:24:08,721
Son!

223
00:24:15,398 --> 00:24:18,663
I swear I'll kill the son of a bitch
who did this.

224
00:24:19,702 --> 00:24:21,636
I swear, son.

225
00:24:45,161 --> 00:24:47,721
It seems that someone let things
get a bit out of hand.

226
00:24:47,931 --> 00:24:50,661
A photographer,
who's a bit queer, you see?

227
00:24:50,834 --> 00:24:53,325
But he doesn't really do
any harm to anyone.

228
00:24:53,837 --> 00:24:57,705
With dead kids you don't make money.
And people get nervous.

229
00:24:58,007 --> 00:24:59,838
So, do you know who it was?

230
00:25:00,210 --> 00:25:03,270
You wouldn't want to bump
the photographer off, would you?

231
00:25:03,446 --> 00:25:07,212
What are you saying?
No, I'd take the backhander,

232
00:25:07,317 --> 00:25:09,945
but murder,
that's something quite different.

233
00:25:10,153 --> 00:25:13,247
I was just asking to know
if Estela's son was mixed up in it.

234
00:25:13,356 --> 00:25:16,484
Don't give me none of that fagot stuff.

235
00:25:17,060 --> 00:25:18,322
There's a man,

236
00:25:18,494 --> 00:25:22,760
with lots of influence,
who's very worried about this thing,

237
00:25:23,333 --> 00:25:27,667
because he's going to lose
a lot of money. You understand?

238
00:25:27,937 --> 00:25:30,633
And the person that sorts this out...

239
00:25:31,007 --> 00:25:33,475
will make a good deal of money.

240
00:25:34,878 --> 00:25:38,211
That Spanish woman you're screwing...

241
00:25:38,514 --> 00:25:40,982
You could give her a nice present.

242
00:25:41,084 --> 00:25:43,177
I don't need to give her presents.

243
00:25:43,586 --> 00:25:46,578
Where's she going to go,
single, with a kid and no house?

244
00:25:46,756 --> 00:25:50,487
As you wish,
but don't give me no crap, right?

245
00:25:51,094 --> 00:25:52,959
Be off with you!

246
00:26:08,244 --> 00:26:10,007
Read all about it!

247
00:26:10,179 --> 00:26:13,046
Boy murdered in Pavón Street!

248
00:26:13,349 --> 00:26:15,544
Read all about it!

249
00:26:15,919 --> 00:26:18,683
<i>A disgusting, brutal crime!</i>

250
00:26:29,198 --> 00:26:32,031
I thought we could at least
