Excuse me.

751
01:13:01,788 --> 01:13:05,280
You are the father of the girl
who burnt to death, aren't you?

752
01:13:35,555 --> 01:13:37,546
Cayetano, someone's coming!

753
01:13:44,731 --> 01:13:47,666
Shit, it's you, you son of a bitch!

754
01:13:52,739 --> 01:13:55,037
I'll skin you alive!

755
01:14:07,154 --> 01:14:10,851
Fiore, did Cayetano come home?

756
01:14:12,759 --> 01:14:15,125
Awhile ago.

757
01:14:16,797 --> 01:14:18,389
What's he done now?

758
01:14:21,701 --> 01:14:23,134
Where did you put my money?

759
01:14:30,377 --> 01:14:33,710
Little bloody devil!

760
01:14:34,181 --> 01:14:36,342
Come here, come here!

761
01:14:42,789 --> 01:14:46,748
That boy's a devil! He's a devil!

762
01:14:46,960 --> 01:14:49,485
It's because of the attacks
that torment him!

763
01:14:51,097 --> 01:14:52,291
Come here!

764
01:14:52,499 --> 01:14:54,399
Little bastard, come here!

765
01:15:02,709 --> 01:15:04,734
Mum! Mum!

766
01:15:05,245 --> 01:15:07,577
What's wrong, son?
What's wrong?

767
01:15:07,881 --> 01:15:09,644
I know who is the murderer.

768
01:15:09,983 --> 01:15:11,348
I saw him.

769
01:15:12,886 --> 01:15:15,150
<i>Read all about it!</i>

770
01:15:15,355 --> 01:15:17,846
<i>The streets are not safe!</i>

771
01:15:18,058 --> 01:15:21,516
<i>The police are covering up
the killer of children!</i>

772
01:15:21,728 --> 01:15:23,457
<i>Read all about it!</i>

773
01:15:23,663 --> 01:15:26,097
<i>The streets are not safe!</i>

774
01:15:26,299 --> 01:15:30,099
The police are covering up
the killer of children!

775
01:15:45,518 --> 01:15:47,179
Are you sure?

776
01:15:54,127 --> 01:15:57,688
I know him, too.
He lives in the neighborhood.

777
01:15:58,865 --> 01:16:01,356
I once met his mother in Lupoff's store.

778
01:16:02,168 --> 01:16:05,160
She told me he'd just come out
of the Marcos Paz reformatory.

779
01:16:07,741 --> 01:16:10,369
More or less
when the nightmares started?

780
01:16:10,944 --> 01:16:12,639
Yes, that's right.

781
01:16:13,513 --> 01:16:16,243
About two months ago.

782
01:16:17,150 --> 01:16:18,549
Here he is.

783
01:16:19,519 --> 01:16:21,419
Cayetano Santos Godino.

784
01:16:21,488 --> 01:16:23,922
He lives at General Urquiza 370.

785
01:16:25,125 --> 01:16:26,717
He was a witness...

786
01:16:27,093 --> 01:16:29,653
to an attack on a boy
who was beaten to death.

787
01:16:31,298 --> 01:16:33,163
The case was never solved.

788
01:16:36,970 --> 01:16:40,269
He was also a witness
in another unsolved case.

789
01:16:43,376 --> 01:16:45,276
A boy burnt on the eyelids.

790
01:16:45,812 --> 01:16:47,336
Very good, Palacios.

791
01:16:47,914 --> 01:16:50,747
Have someone take the lady
and the boy home.

792
01:16:50,951 --> 01:16:52,976
We'll go to Urquiza Street.

793
01:17:12,539 --> 01:17:15,997
Excuse me,
does Cayetano Santos Godino live here?

794
01:17:26,853 --> 01:17:28,650
Yes, he lives here.

795
01:17:28,888 --> 01:17:30,913
But he's not here right now.

796
01:17:33,393 --> 01:17:35,418
Who are you, the police?

797
01:17:37,330 --> 01:17:38,627
May l?

798
01:17:42,602 --> 01:17:44,263
Where does the boy sleep?

799
01:17:45,071 --> 01:17:47,437
There, in the little bed.

800
01:17:53,146 --> 01:17:55,046
He run away last night.

801
01:17:56,282 --> 01:17:58,375
We can't cope with him any more.

802
01:18:00,387 --> 01:18:02,082
Take him away.

803
01:18:03,123 --> 01:18:05,353
Take him to the reformatory.

804
01:18:07,060 --> 01:18:09,358
We don't want him any more.

805
01:18:15,335 --> 01:18:19,499
This time it's because of
the robbery of old Blas, isn't it?

806
01:18:20,073 --> 01:18:22,439
Petrie, come and see this.

807
01:18:36,322 --> 01:18:38,256
Those marbles are nice.

808
01:18:39,692 --> 01:18:42,058
When I was little
I liked them a lot too.

809
01:18:51,704 --> 01:18:53,035
Do you want it?

810
01:18:54,307 --> 01:18:55,865
Do you?

811
01:19:00,380 --> 01:19:02,871
If you want a bigger one, this big,

812
01:19:03,183 --> 01:19:05,413
come with me, I've got more.
Do you want one?

813
01:19:21,568 --> 01:19:22,899
This is it.

814
01:19:27,740 --> 01:19:29,264
Come in.

815
01:19:29,843 --> 01:19:31,708
I've got the big sweet in here.

816
01:19:40,053 --> 01:19:41,680
Where's the sweet?

817
01:19:43,690 --> 01:19:46,250
There, under that metal sheet there.

818
01:20:02,542 --> 01:20:05,409
Help! Help!
Somebody help me!

819
01:20:05,578 --> 01:20:07,170
Please, help me!

820
01:20:39,812 --> 01:20:41,279
Stop, Cayetano!

821
01:20:44,817 --> 01:20:46,307
Are you speaking to me?

822
01:20:50,190 --> 01:20:51,817
What's wrong with you?

823
01:20:52,158 --> 01:20:55,286
What? You're dead?

824
01:20:59,065 --> 01:21:00,293
You're dead!

825
01:21:00,400 --> 01:21:03,665
You're dead, you're dead!

826
01:21:09,008 --> 01:21:10,635
Were you calling? What's wrong?

827
01:21:10,810 --> 01:21:13,244
He had an attack,
but it's over now.

828
01:21:13,413 --> 01:21:14,812
Poor kid.

829
01:21:14,914 --> 01:21:17,474
Please, help me carry him
into the bedroom.

830
01:21:19,185 --> 01:21:20,880
Why did you die?

831
01:21:23,890 --> 01:21:26,085
Don't you want to be my friend
no more?

832
01:21:28,761 --> 01:21:31,525
Well, if you're not going
to speak to me, I'm off.

833
01:21:35,902 --> 01:21:39,599
If you want to get out of here,
tell your mummy to come and help you.

834
01:21:53,353 --> 01:21:54,615
Gesualdo!

835
01:21:56,956 --> 01:21:59,220
Where have you been?

836
01:22:04,330 --> 01:22:07,822
Excuse me, you haven't seen a boy
of about five years old, have you?

837
01:22:08,101 --> 01:22:09,363
He's called Gesualdo.

838
01:22:09,669 --> 01:22:10,931
No.

839
01:22:11,304 --> 01:22:14,000
But don't worry.
You go to the police station,

840
01:22:14,107 --> 01:22:16,598
they'll tell you what to do,
and I'll look for him round here.

841
01:22:17,543 --> 01:22:19,477
Thanks. Thanks.

842
01:22:48,174 --> 01:22:50,108
He told us he was weak.

843
01:23:09,962 --> 01:23:11,395
Excuse me, sir.

844
01:23:11,664 --> 01:23:14,758
This man has come to report
the disappearance of another boy.

845
01:23:15,168 --> 01:23:17,534
Show him into my office immediately.

846
01:23:20,573 --> 01:23:21,835
May l?

847
01:23:22,208 --> 01:23:23,505
Come in.

848
01:23:27,380 --> 01:23:28,574
Sit down.

849
01:23:42,762 --> 01:23:44,389
Do you know that boy?

850
01:23:49,502 --> 01:23:51,197
I don't know him,

851
01:23:52,638 --> 01:23:54,538
but I've just spoken to him.

852
01:23:56,809 --> 01:23:59,243
He told me he'd help me
look for Gesualdo.

853
01:23:59,812 --> 01:24:02,303
Could you take us to the place
where you met him?

854
01:24:03,950 --> 01:24:05,281
Of course.

855
01:24:05,518 --> 01:24:07,918
Don't take him!

856
01:24:08,121 --> 01:24:09,918
Please, don't take him!

857
01:24:10,323 --> 01:24:13,986
Hand the body over to the family.
He's already suffered enough.

858
01:24:14,293 --> 01:24:15,817
I'll take charge.

859
01:24:16,162 --> 01:24:19,029
I don't know if you're still interested.

860
01:24:19,465 --> 01:24:23,128
An informer told me the address
of Cebrián's client.

861
01:24:39,419 --> 01:24:41,785
-Please don't take him!
-Don't worry.

862
01:24:41,854 --> 01:24:43,719
Don't worry.
The superintendent told me...

863
01:24:43,923 --> 01:24:45,948
The superintend told me
you can take him home.

864
01:24:46,159 --> 01:24:47,888
Thank you.

865
01:24:51,998 --> 01:24:55,593
What have they done to you,
my little boy?

866
01:25:12,351 --> 01:25:14,376
<i>-Who is it?
-Superintendent Petrie.</i>

867
01:25:26,566 --> 01:25:28,500
Mateo had another attack,
didn't he?

868
01:25:28,701 --> 01:25:29,861
Yes.

869
01:25:31,170 --> 01:25:33,331
Cayetano has killed another child.

870
01:25:36,943 --> 01:25:39,434
Would you mind if I saw the boy?

871
01:25:40,012 --> 01:25:41,445
No, not at all.

872
01:25:41,948 --> 01:25:44,143
He had a nose bleed again.

873
01:25:45,551 --> 01:25:47,041
He's in there.

874
01:25:58,130 --> 01:25:59,757
How are you doing, friend?

875
01:26:00,032 --> 01:26:01,590
Tired.

876
01:26:06,439 --> 01:26:07,997
Does your stomach hurt?

877
01:26:08,574 --> 01:26:10,064
A bit.

878
01:26:13,145 --> 01:26:17,411
Mateo, you're the only one I can trust.

879
01:26:18,317 --> 01:26:21,252
Cayetano has escaped,
and as he knows we've discovered him,

880
01:26:21,354 --> 01:26:23,481
he almost certainly won't go back home.

881
01:26:23,689 --> 01:26:25,418
I don't know where to look for him.

882
01:26:25,491 --> 01:26:28,085
We've asked around,
no one knows anything.

883
01:26:28,294 --> 01:26:29,852
There's a boy.

884
01:26:30,796 --> 01:26:32,491
He's called Roque.

885
01:26:33,065 --> 01:26:34,930
They're friends.

886
01:26:36,035 --> 01:26:39,266
He lives near Marcial,
two blocks from here.

887
01:26:41,908 --> 01:26:43,170
Thanks.

888
01:26:59,458 --> 01:27:00,857
Lady.

889
01:27:05,231 --> 01:27:07,927
I'm very sorry I didn't believe
your son from the start.

890
01:27:08,034 --> 01:27:09,729
No, don't worry.

891
01:27:09,936 --> 01:27:12,097
You've been very kind to us.

892
01:27:17,043 --> 01:27:19,034
You deserve it, lady.

893
01:27:19,478 --> 01:27:20,945
Good night.

894
01:27:31,891 --> 01:27:33,552
We don't know where the boy is,

895
01:27:33,759 --> 01:27:37,957
but Roque said he'd go to the wake
of that boy who was killed.

896
01:27:39,632 --> 01:27:42,362
My God, if they don't do
something about this...

897
01:27:42,501 --> 01:27:45,265
we're going to have
to tie our kids to the doors.

898
01:28:16,769 --> 01:28:19,237
-Who is it?
-Where's the murderer?

899
01:28:19,372 --> 01:28:21,340
-Where's the boy?
-What are you talking about?

900
01:28:21,440 --> 01:28:22,998
<i>Your son!</i>

901
01:28:25,177 --> 01:28:27,236
<i>Come on, he's getting away!</i>

902
01:28:52,138 --> 01:28:55,505
Die! Die, you son of a bitch!

903
01:29:03,916 --> 01:29:05,474
Cayetano Santos Godino.

904
01:29:08,054 --> 01:29:09,316
What is it?

905
01:29:09,889 --> 01:29:11,823
You're going to have to come with us.

906
01:29:13,059 --> 01:29:15,220
Die! Die, son of a bitch!

907
01:29:38,484 --> 01:29:42,045
My love!
No, my darling, no!

908
01:29:45,591 --> 01:29:47,650
No, my love, no.

909
01:30:41,547 --> 01:30:42,980
What's up?

910
01:30:45,985 --> 01:30:48,283
Tonight I just want to get drunk.

911
01:30:52,391 --> 01:30:55,554
You said it. What good is talking?
Life's a bitch.

912
01:30:59,398 --> 01:31:04,062
I remember after killing that boy,

913
01:31:06,205 --> 01:31:07,638
Arturo,

914
01:31:10,476 --> 01:31:13,673
I went to the shed and I masturbated,

915
01:31:16,715 --> 01:31:19,081
Like when I killed Josefina.

916
01:31:19,985 --> 01:31:23,079
Don't you feel any remorse
for what you did?

917
01:31:26,025 --> 01:31:28,585
I don't understand
what you're asking me.

918
01:31:29,361 --> 01:31:31,693
You don't know what remorse is?

919
01:31:34,600 --> 01:31:36,067
No, sir.

920
01:31:37,603 --> 01:31:40,436
Do you think you have the right
to kill children?

921
01:31:41,106 --> 01:31:42,971
But I'm not the only one,

922
01:31:43,843 --> 01:31:45,868
there are others that do it as well.

923
01:31:50,349 --> 01:31:51,907
Why did you kill them?

924
01:31:52,117 --> 01:31:54,415
Because I like it.

925
01:31:56,422 --> 01:31:57,821
And the wake?

926
01:32:00,659 --> 01:32:03,492
You went to the wake
of the last child you killed.

927
01:32:04,797 --> 01:32:06,059
I wanted to see him.

928
01:32:06,265 --> 01:32:07,459
Why?

929
01:32:09,869 --> 01:32:12,838
I wanted to see
if he had the nail in his head.

930
01:32:37,096 --> 01:32:39,087
You still love me.

931
01:32:40,766 --> 01:32:43,633
No, Octavio, not anymore.

932
01:32:54,847 --> 01:32:57,281
Have you ever tried to strangle a man?

933
01:32:58,617 --> 01:33:02,815
No, no. Men are too big, and I can't.

934
01:33:05,057 --> 01:33:07,548
Well, if I find him asleep, yes.

935
01:33:09,361 --> 01:33:11,625
What do you feel
when you strangle someone?

936
01:33:15,067 --> 01:33:16,329
I don't know.

937
01:33:17,536 --> 01:33:18,935
I like it.

938
01:33:24,209 --> 01:33:26,575
My whole body shakes...

939
01:33:28,781 --> 01:33:31,045
Like if I want to bite.

940
01:33:31,383 --> 01:33:34,944
The way I did with that boy,
I sank my teeth into him like a dog...

941
01:33:37,389 --> 01:33:39,687
Then, I'm thirsty...

942
01:33:41,593 --> 01:33:44,460
and my throat burns
as if I had a fever.

943
01:34:11,557 --> 01:34:12,956
I'm sorry.

944
01:34:14,793 --> 01:34:16,727
I'm so sorry.

945
01:34:18,897 --> 01:34:21,024
The culprit has already paid for it.

946
01:34:22,534 --> 01:34:24,764
That's not justice, Estela.

947
01:34:25,738 --> 01:34:27,467
That's revenge.

948
01:34:29,508 --> 01:34:31,635
For us there never can be justice.

949
01:34:31,910 --> 01:34:33,969
I'll make do with revenge.

950
01:34:50,996 --> 01:34:52,691
One more question.

951
01:34:54,099 --> 01:34:55,896
Have you ever cried?

952
01:34:57,936 --> 01:35:01,269
No, l...

953
01:35:05,577 --> 01:35:07,044
Yes...

954
01:35:07,846 --> 01:35:09,404
Once,

955
01:35:11,583 --> 01:35:15,383
when I wanted to kill a boy
and he escaped.

956
01:35:48,353 --> 01:35:51,481
<i>The victims of Little Big-Ears!</i>

957
01:35:51,690 --> 01:35:54,386
<i>Buenos Aires awash with blood!</i>

958
01:35:54,526 --> 01:35:59,088
<i>Read all about it!
The victims of Little Big-Ears!</i>

959
01:36:04,002 --> 01:36:07,995
Read all about it!
Read all about it!

960
01:36:08,941 --> 01:36:12,206
<i>The victims of Little Big-Ears!</i>

961
01:36:12,444 --> 01:36:15,072
<i>Buenos Aires awash with blood!</i>

962
01:36:31,597 --> 01:36:34,964
Cayetano Santos Godino,
"El Petiso Orejudo" ("Little Big-Ears")

963
01:36:35,167 --> 01:36:37,135
died 32 years later...

964
01:36:37,236 --> 01:36:39,932
in the "Fin del Mundo" prison,
Ushuaia, Argentina.

